32.body: valence-contracts is a flake-parts module that sets up all valence contracts to be uploaded for the latest release to be consumed by the upload-contracts module. It can also create packages for any number of valence-protocol versions with the builds option. This feature is used by zero.nix itself to provide packages for all valence-protocol releases and the main branch.
32.breadcrumbs: Flake Modules Reference » Valence Contracts Options » Valence Contracts
32.title: Valence Contracts

33.body:
To use these options, add to your flake inputs: valence-contracts.url = "github:timewave-computer/zero.nix"; and inside the mkFlake: imports = [ inputs.valence-contracts.flakeModules.valence-contracts
]; Run nix flake lock and you're set.
33.breadcrumbs: Flake Modules Reference » Valence Contracts Options » » Installation
33.title: Installation

34.breadcrumbs: Flake Modules Reference » Valence Contracts Options » » Options

]; Run nix flake lock and you're set.
